&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Guy’s &amp; St Thomas’ NHS Foundation Trust and King’s College London&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The R&amp;D department are recruiting two , fixed-term for 12 months, Research Governance Facilitators. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The R&amp;D Department at Guy’s &amp; St Thomas’ NHS Foundation Trust (GSTT) is one of the focal points for innovative research in London through its nationally recognised research portfolio and research infrastructure. The broad ranging portfolio includes one of only five National Institute for Health Research (NIHR) Biomedical Research Centres in partnership with our academic partner King’s College London, numerous NIHR Programme and Project Grants, as well as a Research Scheme for academic consultants. In addition the Trust is a stakeholder in the newly accredited Academic Health Sciences Centre, King’s Health Partners, and also the Joint Clinical Trials Office and the R&amp;D Department also supports the recently established Clinical Research Facilities. As well as hosting the South London Comprehensive Local Research Network (CLRN), the Trust is a major player in the South London network both in relation to the national research study portfolio and accruals into studies. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This dynamic, lively and diverse department has the breadth of knowledge and skills to ensure that this high level of research activity and associated research processes are managed smoothly and efficiently. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;These posts will be supporting the Research Governance Specialists and R&amp;D Contract Manager in the approval of non-commercial research projects and their amendments. The successful candidates will be an experienced administrators with excellent communication and organisation skills, with a great attention to detail. While experience in clinical research governance, research contracts or clinical trials would be advantageous, full training will also be provided. The selected candidates must work well within a team, whilst being able to work autonomously and manage their time productively. It is necessary for the candidates to liaise with a variety of people but in the current circumstances will be working from home rather than office-based, although this may change according to government guidelines. They must maintain a proactive and positive attitude towards their workload and have a strong interest in research and development processes. In line with current government guidance these posts will initially be (UK) home-based but this may change in line with Trust and government guidelines. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Informal inquiries about this post can be made to Rachel Fay, Research Governance Manager: rachel.fay@gstt.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameRachel FayJob titleResearch Governance ManagerEmail addressrachel.fay@gstt.nhs.ukAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note interviews will be held by MS Teams.&lt;/p&gt;
